{"cursor":"3026","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox building |name = Nyayo House |image = Raidarmax 19789.jpg |caption =\nNyayo House, Nairobi |completion_date = |building_type = Government Building\n|location = Nairobi, Kenya |coordinates = |antenna_spire = |top_floor = |roof =\n|floor_count = 27 |floor_area = |elevator_count = |architect =\n| main_contractor = Laxmanbhai Construction\n}} 'Nyayo House' in a skyscraper in Nairobi, Kenya. It hosts several government\ndepartments such as immigration and also serves as the headquarters of Nairobi\nProvince. The building is located on the corner of Uhuru Highway and Kenyatta\nAvenue. Daily Nation, May 5, 2012 [http://www.nation.co.ke/News/-/1056/1400370/-/yep6qyz/-\n/index.html Inside the walls of the house that kept Kenyaâs dark secrets]\nIt is 84 metres high and has 27 floors http://skyscraperpage.com\n[http://skyscraperpage.com/cities/?buildingID=23986 Nyayo House]\n\nPlanning of the tower started in 1973 and it was initially set to be named as\nNairobi House. Construction started in 1979, one year after Daniel arap Moi took\nover as the president of Kenya. Building of the house was completed in 1983. The\nbuilding was planned by Ministry of Public Works Ngotho Architects and\nconstructed by Laxmanbhai Construction.\n\nNyayo House is particularly known for its detention facilities in its basement,\noften called as \"Nyayo House torture chambers\". Many opponents of the Moi\ngovernment were beaten there by Special Branch officials (the Special Branch has\nlater been renamed National Security Intelligence Service). Some of the known detainees at Nyayo House were George Anyona, Wahome Mutahi\nand Raila Odinga [http://library.fes.de/pdf-files/bueros/kenia/01828.pdf We\nlived to tell - The Nyayo House Story]\n\nAfter the Moi era the Truth, Justice and Reconciliation Commission (TJRC) has\ninvestigated Nyayo House torture cases and several victims, including politician\nKoigi wa Wamwere have been compensated. Another detainee,\nmusician Ochieng Kabaselleh died soon after he was released, allegedly due to\ninjuries caused by torture. The Standard [http://www.standardmedia.co.ke/In-\nsidePage.php?id=2000053608&cid=159&story=%20Cells%20may%20have%20been%20part%20-\nof%20Nyayo%20House%20plan Cells may have been part of Nyayo House plan]\nThe former torture chambers have now been opened to the general public.\n\nNyoyo House is also infamous for the amount for corruption by various state\nofficials.\n","linknr":118,"url":"Nyayo_House","recorded":1375087022,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Nyayo_House&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Nyayo_House&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Raidarmax_19789.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cf/Raidarmax_19789.jpg/220px-Raidarmax_19789.jpg","/wiki/Nairobi","/wiki/Kenya","/w/index.php?title=Laxmanbhai_Construction&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Skyscraper","/wiki/Nairobi","/wiki/Kenya","/wiki/Nairobi_Province","/w/index.php?title=Uhuru_Highway&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=Kenyatta_Avenue&action=edit&redlink=1","#cite_note-secrets-1","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Daniel_arap_Moi","/w/index.php?title=Laxmanbhai_Construction&ac